  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and grate your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained</strong> <strong>mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/extra-easy-margherita-pizza-with-chilli-oil-and-cucumber-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put a large baking tray (or two!) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pizza bottom from going soggy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>paste</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add 5 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[7 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[10 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water </strong>and stir it all together – this is your <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>base</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/extra-easy-margherita-pizza-with-chilli-oil-and-cucumber-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad </strong>then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> into batons</p><p>Combine your <strong>balsamic</strong> <strong>vinegar</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>olive</strong> <strong>oil</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>balsamic</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/extra-easy-margherita-pizza-with-chilli-oil-and-cucumber-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add your <strong>pizza</strong> <strong>base[s]</strong></p><p>Spread the<strong> tomato base</strong> evenly with the back of a spoon over the <strong>pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>torn</strong> <strong>mozzarella</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/extra-easy-margherita-pizza-with-chilli-oil-and-cucumber-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 13-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the base is crisp – this is your<strong> extra easy margherita pizza</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/extra-easy-margherita-pizza-with-chilli-oil-and-cucumber-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the pizza is cooking, heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat for 1-2 min or until very hot</p><p>Add your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a small heatproof bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Carefully pour the <strong>heated oil</strong> into the bowl, give it a good mix up and set aside for later – this is your <strong>chilli oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/extra-easy-margherita-pizza-with-chilli-oil-and-cucumber-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>salad</strong> and <strong>cucumber</strong> <strong>batons</strong> in a bowl with the <strong>balsamic</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Set aside half of the cucumber batons for serving!</span></strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>leafy cucumber salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/extra-easy-margherita-pizza-with-chilli-oil-and-cucumber-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>extra easy margherita pizza</strong> and drizzle over the <strong>chilli</strong> <strong>oil</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!), then tear over your <strong>basil</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>leafy cucumber salad</strong> to the side</p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave the chilli oil and basil and serve the reserved cucumber batons to the side!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
